result.execSummary:
The defendant Jared Robert Denotter was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
1) The Court has waived certain court costs, assessing only the DNA surcharge in this matter.
2) The Court reserves the right to enter a civil judgment against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.
The defendant shall maintain gainful employment.
Defendant shall not use or possess firearms for life.
Defendant shall not vote in any election until their civil rights are restored.

1) If the defendant pays the past due balance owed to Child Support within two years, he may discharge off of probation early.
2) The defendant shall continue to make child support payments as ordered.

02:34 PM Cases 16CF38, 16CF39, and 19CF273 called together. Defendant, Jared Robert Denotter, appeared with Attorney Samuel Louis Lawton.  Attorney Jeffrey Robert Kohler appeared for the State.  All cases on for sentencing hearing.  State argues for 30 days conditional jail via electronic monitoring.  Defense attorney argues for 1-2 years probation or electronic monitoring.  Defendant declines to make a statement.  Court has reviewed PSI.  Court asks for balance due in CS; atty Kohler leaves to get current figures.  Off the record 2:52 PM.  Back on the record 2:58 PM same appearances as previously noted.  Atty Kohler has Exhibit 01: Child Supportment Statement marked, is offered, and received- notes the balance due.  
Court orders: 
16CF38: failure to support- probation for 3 years, withheld; assesses $518 costs; 30 days conditional jail, to start after released from EM on OWI case (must sit 30 full days- EM eligible, not good time eligible). 
16CF39: failure to support- probation for 3 years, withheld; assesses $250 DNA only
19CF273: felony bond jump- probation for 3 years, withheld; assesses $250 DNA only
Conditions: 
If def pays past-due CS in full after two years, can terminate off of probation early.   Continue to make child support payments as ordered.  Maintain gainful employment.  No firearms for life.  No voting until civil rights are restored.  
Bond to apply to court costs.  If any funds are left in AFT or bond after everything is paid, it will be sent to Child Support to apply to his current balance.
Appeal rights provided.  
DNA to be provided to the Sheriff's Department before leaving the building.
Exhibit 01: Child Support Balance

03:48 PM  Called 19TR369, 19TR370, 16CF38, 16CF39, 19CF273, & 19CT21 for PLEAS.  Defendant, Jared Robert Denotter, appeared in person with Attorney Samuel Louis Lawton in person.  Attorney Daniel Patrick Steffen appeared for the State by video. Def waives the right for all parties to be in person. Case is on for Plea/Sentencing Hearing.  Agreement is recited by Attorney Lawton on the record.
Plead guilty to 19CT21; 19TR369 & 19TR37 Dismissed/ DRI, proceed on sentencing today; Plead guilty to 19CF273 today; not enter judgments on 16CF cases, but order a PSI for 16CF38, 16CF39 & 19CF273.  State would stand mute at sentencing in 19CT21.
Court reviews Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights that was filed on 1-18-2021.
Court asks def if they understand the agreement.  Def does.  Court reviews Defs constitutional rights.  Def understands that def is waiving those rights by entering into agreement today.  Court asks Def if they understand Court is not bound by agreement, and could order maximum penalties.  Def understands.  Court asks for plea. 
Def enters a plea of Guilty to count 2: OWI 3rd in 19CT21 and enters a peal of Guilty to Felony Bail Jumping in 19CF273.  Court finds def is making plea knowingly, intelligently and voluntarily.  Court finds a factual basis to accept the plea.  Court finds defendant guilty of OWI 3rd and guilty of a Felony Bail Jump and orders a JOC.  Deferred JOC in 16CF38 & 16CF39 cases.  Court enters Judgement in 16CF38 & 16CF39, both cases, count 1.  Felony counts, PSI long form will be entered, def must have contact with agent to complete.  Regarding the OWI 3rd, State doesn't have anything to add.   Defense attorney argues for Court to follow 10th Judicial District OWI guidelines, additionally argue for remaining time on sentence after 48 consecutive hours in jail to be on electronic monitor, has been in contact with Tessa Anderson, asks Court to accept agreement.  Def does not make statement to the Court.  Court makes a statement.

Court Orders:
$4,026, 110 days of jail, revoke Drivers License for 30 months and IID.
Court will follow 10th district OWI guidelines, def must serve 48 hours consecutive in jail, then will do electronic monitoring - Huber privileges but it is house arrest, if violate then go directly to jail.
Orders payment plan of $200/month, with first payment stayed for 3 months.
Appeal rights provided.  Def must report to jail immediately, Tessa Anderson will set up electronic monitoring Monday.
